rely have made this Nadal's last singles outing at the French Open venue, where he is a 14-time champion, but instead the two-time gold medalist ensured his final Games rumbles on on two fronts, grafting his way to a 6-1 4-6 6-4 in a little more than two-and-a-half hours.\", \"from\": 790, \"to\": 1107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 800, \"end\": 807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999992766959509, \"rank\": 7.233030498117708e-07, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 810, \"end\": 826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/M\\u00e1rton_Fucsovics\", \"score\": 0.9999999956035026, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marton Fucsovics\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/M\\u00e1rton_Fucsovics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/M\\u00e1rton_Fucsovics\"}, {\"begin\": 855, \"end\": 860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9659849840764667e-31, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Defeat\", \"from\": 790, \"to\": 796}, {\"ngram\": \"the French Open venue\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 907}, {\"ngram\": \"a 14-time champion\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 939}, {\"ngram\": \"the two-time gold medalist\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 979}, {\"ngram\": \"his final Games\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 1003}, {\"ngram\": \"two fronts\", \"from\": 1018, \"to\": 1028}, {\"ngram\": \"his way\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1046}, {\"ngram\": \"a little more than two-and-a-half hours\", \"from\": 1067, \"to\": 1106}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having braved the Seine's choppy waters for his starring role in Friday night's Opening Ceremony, and then battled through a men's doubles opener alongside Carlos Alcaraz late on Saturday night, this briefly looked set to be the Nadal's most straightforward task of the Games so far.\", \"from\": 1109, \"to\": 1392, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1127, \"end\": 1132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.604421600244599e-13, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 1189, \"end\": 1205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.7103276527427457, \"rank\": 0.3174712259956926, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}, {\"begin\": 1265, \"end\": 1279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\"}, {\"begin\": 1338, \"end\": 1343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9659849840764667e-31, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his starring role\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1170}, {\"ngram\": \"a men's doubles opener\", \"from\": 1232, \"to\": 1254}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday night\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1302}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1375, \"to\": 1384}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Roared on by a near capacity Court Philippe-Chatrier from his first warm-up volley, the 38-year-old broke at the earliest opportunity to set the tone for a commanding opening set, only for Fucsovics to return the favour at the top of the second.\", \"from\": 1394, \"to\": 1639, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a near capacity\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1422}, {\"ngram\": \"Court Philippe-Chatrier\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1446}, {\"ngram\": \"his first warm-up volley\", \"from\": 1452, \"to\": 1476}, {\"ngram\": \"the earliest opportunity\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1527}, {\"ngram\": \"the tone\", \"from\": 1535, \"to\": 1543}, {\"ngram\": \"a commanding opening set\", \"from\": 1548, \"to\": 1572}, {\"ngram\": \"Fucsovics\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1592}, {\"ngram\": \"the favour\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1613}, {\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1624}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From there, the world No83 repelled every Nadal charge until serving to level the match, then wobbled briefly as the Spaniard wrestled the set back onto serve, only for his double-fault to offer Fucsovics an immediate second opening, this one grabbed.\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1892, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1683, \"end\": 1688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9659849840764667e-31, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}, {\"begin\": 1758, \"end\": 1766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spaniards\", \"score\": 0.9426214583130105, \"rank\": 0.06045561518056293, \"text\": \"Spaniard\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spaniards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spaniards\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1662}, {\"ngram\": \"the match\", \"from\": 1719, \"to\": 1728}, {\"ngram\": \"the set\", \"from\": 1776, \"to\": 1783}, {\"ngram\": \"serve\", \"from\": 1794, \"to\": 1799}, {\"ngram\": \"his double-fault\", \"from\": 1810, \"to\": 1826}, {\"ngram\": \"Fucsovics\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1845}, {\"ngram\": \"an immediate second opening\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1873}, {\"ngram\": \"this one\", \"from\": 1875, \"to\": 1883}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nadal had only made the decision to play singles on Sunday morning, returning to the court fewer than 20 hours after his win alongside Alcaraz, both before and after which he had flirted with the idea of following Murray's lead by focusing on the doubles to ease his workload.\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 2170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1894, \"end\": 1899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9659849840764667e-31, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}, {\"begin\": 2029, \"end\": 2036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.816056037735465e-20, \"text\": \"Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\"}, {\"begin\": 2108, \"end\": 2114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.487921618787751e-62, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 1914, \"to\": 1926}, {\"ngram\": \"singles\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 1942}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday morning\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 1960}, {\"ngram\": \"the court\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 1984}, {\"ngram\": \"his win\", \"from\"